      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De invidia</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e112">De invidia, odium, susurratio, detractio,
              exultatio in adversis proximi, et afflictio in prosperis nascitur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e127">Qui post puniendi sunt retributionis supplicio,
              nunc semetipsos afficiunt invidiae tormento.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e142">Invidia iram generat; quia quanto interno
              livoris vulnere animus sauciatur, tanto etiam mansuetudo tranquillitatis
              amittitur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e157">Dum electi proficiunt, reprobi ad rabiem furoris
              et invidiae excitantur, et bona nascentia, quae nolunt imitari, gravius
              persequuntur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in
              <title>Dialogis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e173">Antiquus hostis, unde bonos cernit per
              charitatem, provehi ad gloriam, inde perversos per invidiam rapit ad poenam.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in
              <title>Homiliis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e188">Quidquid in mundo concupiscimus, hoc proculdubio
              proximis invidemus. Videtur etenim quia nobis desit, quod alius assequitur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e195">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, in <title>Sermonibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e203">O zelus, о invidia omni malitia cumulata!
              Invidia ignis inextinguibilis est; etenim, sicut tinea comedit vestimentum, sic et
              invidia eum, qui zelatur, consumit; eum autem cui invidet, clariorem reddit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e210">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>super Joannem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e218">Invidiae passio, et fornicatione, et adulterio
              multum est deterior.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e225">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>super Joannem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e233">Invidi oculus liquatur tristitia, invidus cum
              morte vivit continua.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e240">Augustinus,
              <title>de Disciplina Christiana</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e248">Avertat Deus invidiae pestem ab animis omnium,
              nedum Christianorum. Vitium enim diabolicum est invidia, quo solo diabolus reus est,
              et inexpiabiliter reus. Non enim dicitur diabolo, ut damnetur: Quia adulterium
              commisisti, furtum fecisti, villam alienam rapuisti; sed: Quia homini stanti, tu
              lapsus, continuo invidisti.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e256">Augustinus,
              <title>de Virginitate</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e264">Superbiam sequitur invidia, tanquam filia et
              pedissequa. Eam quippe superbia continuo parit, nec unquam est superbia sine tali
              prole atque comite. </quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e271">Hieronymus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e279">О invidia primum mordax tui, о satanae
              calliditas semper sancta persequens!</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e284">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e294" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e286">Isidorus, in
              <title>Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e294">Invidia cuncta bona ardore pestifero devorat.
              Invidia, animae tinea, sensum comedit, pectus urit, mentem afficit, cor hominis quasi
              quaedam pestis depascit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e299">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e309" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e301">Anselmus, de
              <title>Similitudinibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e309">Qui bonis alterius arridet, sanctis consentit;
              qui vero invidet, diabolis similis est. Siquidem magis puto esse salvationem sperandam
              ejus, qui parum boni facit, et factis aliorum favet, quam illius, qui multa, et
              invidet aliis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e314">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e324" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e316">Seneca, in
              <title>Proverbiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e324">Nondum felix es, si nondum turba te deridet. Nam
              etsi nullos tibi inimicos facit injuria, multos facit invidia.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-d1e329">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e336" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Rd1e331">Glossa, super
            Psalmum CXXIII</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e14682-Qd1e336">Ira et invidia judicio carent.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
